Package: mrhorse
Title: R Package for Bayesian Mendelian Randomisation with Horseshoe Shrinkage Prior
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Andrew", "Grant", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "andrew.grant1@sydney.edu.au")
Description: Provides functions to perform univariable and multivariable Mendelian randomization. Causal effect estimation is performed in a Bayesian framework using a horseshoe shrinkage prior to account for both correlated and uncorrelated pleiotropic effects.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
